{"author":{"id":"783b610f274a0d93f6239db0fc75d0982606c877a4661d3aea84b42bc3a85cea"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1521150630,"nonce":"+cbL2UZb4nAaSynmIDsbO/cI3S0=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUzMDU3MzE3NTQ=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1774","origin":"github"},"title":"Upgrade tools to output the new bam datatypes","message":"Datasets with a `bam` datatype are now assumed to be intact and coordinate-sorted by tools that consume them. This is not enforced by tools that output BAMs yet.\n\n----\n\nExample: SAM-to-BAM will output a `bam` datatype dataset even when the header does not contain: \n\n`@HD   VN:1.0  SO:coordinate`\n\n**See datasets 8, 13, 14, 15 in test history:** https://usegalaxy.org/u/jen/h/test-history-bam-datatypes This first test had a completely messed up header (no HD line at all) and still produced a green success `bam` dataset. I expected it to fail outright with a UI error message about a format problem. \n\nThe tool might have always done this, but I wanted to show how badly an input can be formatted and still result in a `bam` result -- without the end user knowing what went wrong when downstream tools fail or produce odd results. It would be really good to know that any dataset assigned to `bam` meets the format specification (not just when newly uploaded, but also when produced by tools within Galaxy).\n\nWe already know that several tools will need an update, this is just one example to get things out for comments. I haven't tested at https://usegalaxy.eu and haven't tested on an intact unsorted bam (specified in header). \n\nOther tools that will need an update include SortSam and Sort, probably all mapping tools, plus others that manipulate bam datasets (mostly in Samtools/Picard tool groups). Some examples of current behavior are in same test history above.\n\n\n**Help \"What it does\" section will need an update once the changes are made.** Should reflect this info at a minimum (all four types):\n\n\u003cimg width=\"739\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-03-15 at 2 25 51 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8999735/37492006-e0c8a42a-285c-11e8-95e5-4e50e4afd90c.png\"\u003e\n\n\nWhat do others think about creating a general description of the different new bam datatypes and what they represent that we could add directly to any tool form as static help text? For all tools that output one of these BAM formats? Would avoid the need to update all again if we change how bams are labeled - and make tool forms consistent across tools - and aid our end users is understanding what these new datatypes represent now.\n\nNew bam dataset testing/tracking master issue: https://github.com/galaxyproject/usegalaxy-playbook/issues/102","files":null}]}